Description. Male (Paratype—Barro Colorado Island—AMNH).
Carapace and chelicerae brownish orange (
Fig. 43A
). Endites orange; labium dark orange. Sternum orange, with darker margins, and three pairs of fainted dark marginal areas (
Fig. 43B
). Palps orange (
Fig. 44A‒B
). Legs brownish orange, pairs I‒II darker, with the femur, patella and tibia marbled with fainted dark pigment, and dark diffuse rings in the distal region of metatarsus (
Fig. 43C‒F
). Abdomen grey, lighter ventrally (
Fig. 43A‒B
). Total length 6.24; carapace 3.12 long, 2.32 wide. Palps: tibia incrassated, with the dorso-ventral diameter shorter than the bulb; bulb rounded, midportion shorter than the embolus and directed backwards; mid-portion/embolus transition conspicuous; embolus long and with a tubular tip (
Fig. 44A‒B
). Legs: slender and sparsely coated with setae (
Fig. 43C‒F
); metatarsi IV sinuous, in lateral view (
Fig. 43F
); tarsal brush of putative chemosensory setae present in legs II‒IV, extending to the median region of the metatarsi IV (
Fig. 43F
). Leg formula: I-II-IV-III. Leg measurements: I, femur 3.0, patella 1.2, tibia 2.52, metatarsus 2.72, tarsus 0.72, total 10.16; II, 2.68, 1.12, 2.52, 2.72, 0.76, 9.8; III, 2.08, 0.96, 1.56, 1.68, 0.64, 6.92; IV, 2.4, 1.08, 1.88, 1.68, 0.64, 7.68. Macrosetae: I, femur D0-0-0-1-0-2-0, P0-0-0-0-1-1-0; tibia D0-0-0-0-1-0-0, P0-1-0-1-0-1-0, vp1-0-0-0-0-0-1, vr2-0-1-0-1-0-1, R1-1-1-1-1-1-1; metatarsus p0-1-0-0-0-0-0, vp0-1-0-0-1-0-1, vr0-0-0-0-1-0-1 (
Fig. 43C‒E
); II, femur D0-0-0/1-0/1-0-2-0, P0-0-0-0-1-1-0; tibia D0-0-0-0-0/1- 0-0, P0-1-0-1-0-1-0, vp0-0-0-0-0-1-1, vr2-0-1-0-1-0/1-1, R1-1-0-1-0-1-0; metatarsus p0-1-0-0-0-0-0, vp1-0-0-1-0- 0-1, vr1-0-0-1-0-0-1, r0-0-0/1-0-1/0-0-0; IV, femur D1/0-1-0-0-0-0-0; metatarsus vr metatarsal comb with 4 macrosetae.

Female (Barro Colorado Island—USNM). Coloration as in male; palps orange, gradually darkening to distal direction ( Fig. 43G‒H ). Total length 10.56; carapace 3.8 long, 2.56 wide. Legs: robust and densely coated with setae; legs I‒II with ventro-prolateral and ventro-retrolateral tibial macrosetae of similar size, and metatarsal macrosetae of different sizes (
Fig. 43I ‒J
). Leg formula: I-II-IV-III. Leg measurements: I, femur 2.8, patella 1.32, tibia 2.2, metatarsus 2.0, tarsus 0.68, total 9.0; II, 2.6, 1.32, 2.2, 2.0, 0.68, 8.8; III, 2.04, 1.12, 1.44, 1.44, 0.64, 6.68; IV, 2.44, 1.32, 1.92, 1.6, 0.6, 7.88. Macrosetae: I, femur D0-0-0-0-0-2-0, P0-0-0-2-1-0-0; tibia P0-0-0-1-0-1-0, vp1- 0-1-0-1-0-1, vr1-0-1-0-1-0-1, R0-1-0-1-0-1-0; metatarsus vp1-1-1-1-1-1-1, vr1-1-1-1-1-1-1 (
Fig. 43I ‒J
); II, femur D0-0-0-0-0-2-0, P0-0-0-0-0-1-0; tibia P0-1-0-1-0-1-0, vp0-0-0-1(slender)-0-1-1, vr1-0-1-0-1-0-1, R0-1-0-1-0-1-0; metatarsus vp1-1-1-1-1-1-1, vr1-1-1-1-1-0/1-1-1-1; IV, metatarsus vp0-0-0-0-0-1, vr metatarsal comb with 4 macrosetae. Internal genitalia: anterior receptaculum with short lobes, and glandular plate in the proximal region, expanded laterally ( Fig. 44C‒D ).
